17th Annual DICE Awards nominations led by The Last of Us
The Academy of Interactive Arts and Sciences announced the nominees for the 17th Annual DICE Awards today, to be held during the annual DICE Summit in Las Vegas on Feb. 6.
Topping the list is Naughty Dog's The Last of Us with 13 nominations, including votes for performances by both Troy Baker and Ashley Johnson as Joel and Ellie. Grand Theft Auto 5 received seven nominations while BioShock Infinite received six. Media Molecule's Tearaway and Assassin's Creed 4: Black Flag both received five.
Assassin's Creed 4: Black Flag, BioShock Infinite, Grand Theft Auto 5 and The Last of Us along with The Legend of Zelda: A Link Between Worlds are up for game of the year. Last year, the coveted game of the year award went to thatgamecompany'sJourney.
The entire list contains 24 categories including the new Online Game of the Year award, which recognizes titles launched outside of the current calendar and aims to commemorate the "constantly evolving experiences persistent online titles provide." This year's ceremony, beginning at 10:30 p.m. ET will be livestreamed by DICE.
The full list of nominees is as follows:
